<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[162,778,1161,1551]" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis box="[162,263,1161,1182]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" box="[278,648,1161,1183]" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonn√© &amp; Olu (1996: 287)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the possibility of parapagurid hermit crabs at two locations: cold seeps of the 
<collectingCountry box="[509,617,1222,1244]" name="Barbados" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">Barbados</collectingCountry>
Accretionary Prism (BAP) (probably the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[549,697,1253,1274]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parapaguridae" genus="Parapagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,697,1253,1274]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">Parapagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and a cold seep of Monterey Bay (not identified). The latter record was listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barry JP &amp; Greene HG &amp; Orange DL &amp; Baxter CH &amp; Robison BH &amp; Kochevar RE &amp; Nybakken JW &amp; Reed DL &amp; McHugh CM" box="[402,613,1314,1336]" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" pagination="1739 - 1762" refId="ref61052" refString="Barry JP, Greene HG, Orange DL, Baxter CH, Robison BH, Kochevar RE, Nybakken JW, Reed DL, McHugh CM. 1996. Biologic and geologic characteristics of cold seeps in Monterey Bay, California. Deep-Sea Research I - Oceanographic Research Papers 43: 1739 - 1762." type="journal article" year="1996">
Barry 
<emphasis box="[478,526,1314,1336]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">et al</emphasis>
. (1996)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[655,774,1314,1336]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Paguridae</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1882" box="[305,477,1345,1367]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parapaguridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Parapaguridae</taxonomicName>
. The animals were apparently seen but not collected. These observations constituted the only known records of hermit crabs associated with hydrothermal vents until 
<bibRefCitation author="Lemaitre R" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" pagination="325 - 334" refId="ref70287" refString="Lemaitre R. 2004. Discovery of the first hermit crab (Crustacea: Decapoda: Parapaguridae) associated with hydrothermal vents. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 45: 325 - 334." type="journal article" year="2004">Lemaitre (2004)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Parapaguridae" genus="Paragiopagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">Paragiopagurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Tashi fishing grounds off northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[255,339,1529,1551]" name="Taiwan" pageId="41" pageNumber="486">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
